This article is a Presidential Memorandum from the White House Office of the Press Secretary. It discusses the establishment of an Interagency Task Force on Federal Contracting Opportunities for Small Businesses. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of small businesses participating in the nation's economic recovery and highlights the goals set by Congress for small business participation in federal contracts. It acknowledges that the government has not consistently reached these goals and expresses the commitment to ensuring fair access to federal contracting for small businesses, particularly those owned by women, minorities, socially and economically disadvantaged individuals, and service-disabled veterans. The memorandum orders the establishment of the Interagency Task Force, with the Secretary of Commerce, the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, and the Administrator of the Small Business Administration serving as co-chairs. It also outlines the membership of the task force and its functions, which include providing proposals and recommendations for increasing opportunities for small businesses, removing barriers to participation, expanding outreach strategies, and establishing policies to achieve the objectives of the memorandum. The memorandum also calls for the use of technology to improve transparency and accountability in federal contracting and emphasizes the importance of outreach with small businesses and associations. The memorandum concludes with general provisions regarding implementation and assistance from executive departments and agencies.